##How did the high-priced masks come to market?

Weixin Signal Wowjiemian

Function introduction, the interface news is China has the influence original financial and economic new media, only serves the independent thinking crowd

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Image: Visual China

Reporter: Ke Xiaobin Editor: Wen Shuqi

“

As the outbreak eased, mask prices began to fall.

”

“

As the outbreak eased, mask prices began to fall.

”

With the return to work tide coming, "can not buy a mask" or the problem of office workers.

On e-commerce platforms such as tmall, Jd.com and Suning, consumers can still grab a few masks issued by legitimate medical device manufacturers with quick hands or good luck.

In the more private channels such as wechat business, medical masks also appear from time to time, but the price is generally expensive.

After the outbreak of the epidemic, to ensure the normal use of front-line medical staff, masks as medical materials were brought into the system under the direct management of the government. On January 29, the State Council issued the State Council General Office, an urgent notice on organizing the resumption of work and scheduling of enterprises producing key materials for epidemic prevention and control.

The circular stipulates that all provincial (regional and municipal) Government of the People's Republic of China should promptly organize the local production and use of related drug enterprises to resume production. At the same time, the material support group of the joint prevention and control mechanism of the COVID-19 shall be responsible for the unified management and unified allocation of the prevention and control materials.

Under such background, how does the high price mask flow to the market?

###As raw materials go up, manufacturers don't actually make money

After the Spring Festival, Chen Ming (not his real name) , who originally intended to donate money, decided to put his mask into production.

Together with several friends, he raised 2 million yuan and set up two production lines of face masks in a city in Guangdong Province. After he decided to switch production, he spent one million yuan to buy two mask machines, because they mainly produce surgical masks, need to build more than 100,000 clean workshop, at the same time need to be equipped with a laboratory, the production of face masks for sampling inspection, quality Assurance. "It also cost about 500,000 yuan to set up a sterile workshop and buy the equipment. "

"It only took a week or so to go from the registered company to the official production, " Chen said, adding that because it is a medical materials manufacturer, the registered company went through the Green Channel and the whole process took only about a day to complete. After the production of mask samples, after the relevant unit testing, mask quality standards, immediately received the production, business license.

At present, they have a total of 50 workers on the assembly line, the average daily output of 200,000 or so. "The factory is manned 24 hours by personnel from relevant government functional units, and each batch of masks produced is pulled away by them and distributed uniformly, " Chen said.

On February 7, at a press conference on the prevention and control of the epidemic held by the Information Office of the Guangdong Provincial Government, Tu Gaokun, director-general of the Department of Industry and Information Technology of Guangdong Province, said that for manufacturers of medical protective clothing, medical protective masks and medical masks, the maximum incentive for the acquisition of equipment to increase production capacity is 80 per cent of the purchase value.

"The subsidy is between 50% and 80% , and the policy varies from district to district, but it is not clear when the subsidy will be given, " Chen said.

The masks requisitioned by the local government are paid to Chen Ming at cost. But at the same time, there was more competition, and raw materials began to soar.

With face masks in short supply, there is no shortage of new entrants to the industry. According to the third-party platform sky eye survey, based on business registration change information, from January 1 to February 7,2020, there are more than 3000 enterprises in China, which have added the business of "face mask, protective clothing, disinfectant, temperature measuring instrument and medical instrument" . Among them, the business scope of new medical devices as many as 3647 enterprises.

According to Chen Ming, with the mask became a must, the price of the mask machine has also gone up, from 100,000 a year ago to now 500,000 a set, and even some suppliers have bid up the price to more than 1 million.

"As one of the main raw materials for the production of face masks, the price of meltblown cloth on Feb. 12 was 35 yuan per kilogram, and a week later it was 290 yuan per kilogram, " Chen said, adding that the wages of workers returning to work at special stages were also higher than usual, this has resulted in the production cost of masks being several times higher than before.

"In the past, it cost less than 0.2 yuan to produce a medical surgical mask, but now it may cost more than 1 yuan, " Chen said, adding that manufacturers could actually lose money if the masks were all purchased by the government at cost.

###Hedging losses, some masks to the market

To hedge against losses, regular manufacturers are selling some masks on their own, as well as meeting government purchases.

Interface journalists entered a wechat group called "mutual help group" , where daily people still share information about group-buying masks.

Citing the need to purchase face masks in batches for the resumption of work by the enterprise, the reporter contacted a middleman, who sent the reporter the relevant production and business licenses of the two companies, and said that relatives were in the company's contracted workshop, four cases of 20,000 masks will be distributed that day. "these masks have company seals, quality inspection reports, and shipping manifests. We can issue them to Eastern Airlines or SF express. We all pay a deposit at the factory. "

Zhang Bin (not his real name) , who was once involved in government procurement in a certain area of Hubei Province, told interface news that before the unified management of the government, some enterprises worked overtime to produce masks in order to withdraw funds, after meeting the needs of the government, some of it is sold through online channels.

In addition to large factories, a large number of small mask workshops are also in such a state.

"China's mask production still accounts for 50 percent of the world's total. Mask enterprises are mainly located in the Yangtze River Delta, Pearl River Delta, Xiantao County in Hubei Province and Tongcheng county in Anhui Province. There are more than 20 well-known mask enterprises, while Xiantao county in Hubei Province has more than 3,000 mask enterprises and is an industrial cluster. However, more than 95 percent of Xiantao mask enterprises are export-oriented, with small family-style workshops and one factory per factory, " Liu Hongbin, director of the National Labor Protection Products Quality Supervision and Inspection Center (Wuhan) , told the China Times.

Zhang said masks are medical supplies, and before the outbreak, the state controlled their production and business licenses more strictly, and many enterprises could not get the relevant complete procedures in the past, only small workshops model production. The companies themselves do not have enough cash flow and are less risk-averse, so they may find ways to sell some of their masks themselves.

"At present, the masks in circulation in the market are mainly made by overseas agents or small workshops, " Liu Chenglong, marketing director of Shenzhen China Nepstar, told interface news, the two big factories they used to dock with said they could no longer supply, so they had to find alternative channels.

###Prices are falling

As of February 22, China's daily production of face masks had reached 54.77 million, National Development and Reform Commission Secretary General Cong Liang said at a press conference held by the Guoxin Administration on Feb. 24. The total number of masks produced in the past 20 days has reached 570 million, Capacity utilization has reached 110% .

Previously, interface news calculated that 238 million people would need to wear face masks every day if work resumed in the secondary sector of the economy, medical care, transportation and other sectors; if it did, according to the fourth national economic census, a total of 533 million people are employed by legal entities and self-employed households in the country. At the rate of one mask per person per day, at least 533 million masks are required per day.

As a result, the gap in mask demand remains. But in Chen's view, as the epidemic is brought under control nationwide, the mask panic will gradually improve.

"Now the high-priced face masks may return to their original prices by the end of March, while those who sell them will face a situation where they can not be resold, " Chen said.

Ms. Wang, who lives in Chaoyang District, Beijing, found that mask prices had fallen in some wechat channels.

The wechat business she knows has taken the initiative to sell masks. KF94 in South Korea now costs $23 and disposable surgical masks $4.90, starting at 100 in Florida. Although still expensive, two weeks ago the same person was selling KF94 for $32, the latter requires a minimum of 1,000 units.

Liu Chenglong, marketing director of China Nepstar, said that previously, because the sales of face masks accounted for a negligible proportion of the sales of its entire pharmacy, during the outbreak, demand was so high that it could not keep up with demand. But as the outbreak abates, the supply of masks will return to normal.
